## 4. Carrington Event Business Continuity V2.0

### 4.1 GIC Impact on Physical Amusement Operations

A G5 geomagnetic event induces GICs that can:
- Destroy point-of-sale (POS) terminal electronics (metal-chassis, copper-wired)
- Disable cellular payment networks (base stations lose grid power)
- Corrupt cloud AI agent memory states (satellite link interruption)
- Heat conductive machine housings → customer burn risk

**V2.0 Resiliency Protocol:**
1. All claw machine control electronics: BFRP-encased, MXene-shielded (SE=92 dB)
2. Payment: offline-first cash mode + local SQLite transaction log
3. AI agents: local MRAM-stored fallback rules ("if coin inserted, operate machine")
4. Power: LiFePO4 UPS per machine (2 kWh, 4-hour backup)
5. Communications: LoRa mesh allows location manager to check status without internet

